{
  "stem": "24409.5",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I'm running out of money.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I need money from the rich British Jews.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they gave me a visa in which was written for visit, for tourist only.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the intention, of course, was the moment I'm not a tourist, only then arrest me and say, help me.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my intention was never to go to Britain.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But with the British visa, which was a very good visa, at the other end of Europe, I could get transit visas through all the countries on the way.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this is how I got my Italian visa, my Swiss visa, because I could be sent to Britain.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Britain has given me a regular visa.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Switzerland I met Dr.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Hecht, who was the Irgun representative for Europe.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we discussed what can we do.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And from the first moment, we clicked.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We have remained very good friends all our lives.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We clicked, we suit each other very well.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He comes from a very well-to-do Swiss family.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "His father owned the Swiss German Danube shipping company.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And much of the shipping which went down and up the Danube went through his ships.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he was a Zionist, and a religionist.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And his father was very much against Zionism.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And his father Hecht was about to initiate a procedure to declare him mentally sick, so that he cannot he couldn't make debts on the name of Hecht, which was a big name in-- Hecht in Switzerland at this time was like Rockefeller here.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "His father was a lot like Rockefeller here, but a very well-known rich man.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And with his name, we had many advantages with the police, with the Swiss police.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we decided, why should we have ships for 800 people?",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
